1H Trading Update Summary:
- 1H 2025 revenue guidance: $40–45m (includes $12m AUD from resolved Middle East contract).
- Expected near-term cash receipt: ~$60m AUD (US$40m) from the same contract.
- FY2025 revenue: Still weighted to 2H; expected from existing backlog ($170m, up from $136m at Dec-2024) and pending new contracts.
- Market backdrop: Strong demand for counter-drone products due to geopolitical tensions; advanced sales pipeline.

Key Risks: Revenue timing uncertain due to contract milestones and customer delays.

Omitted: Operational details without material impact, forward-looking disclaimers.

Summary of ASX Announcement:

Announcement Type: Operational Update

Material Information:

  • Production Capacity Doubled: Two new DirectPowder™ units commissioned at Neighborhood 91 facility, doubling operational capacity (on budget/on schedule).
  • Automation Achieved: DirectPowder™ process now fully automated, enabling 24/7 "lights out" production, reducing costs, and accelerating delivery times.
  • Strategic Impact: Expected to drive order growth in high-strength aluminum/copper alloys and key sectors (defense, aerospace, energy).

No capital markets activity (e.g., raising, halt) or financial metrics (e.g., cash balance) disclosed.

• Milestone Payment Received: Dimerix received ¥400 million (~AU$4.2 million) from FUSO Pharmaceutical for initiating clinical sites in Japan.
  • Potential Future Payments: Up to ¥10.5 billion (~AU$107 million) in total milestone payments (development + sales) and 15-20% royalties on net sales from FUSO.
  • Total Licensing Deals: Over AU$65 million received to date across four regional licensing agreements, with potential for ~AU$1.4 billion in total milestone payments plus royalties.
  • ACTION3 Trial Progress: Japanese sites will recruit ~20 patients for FSGS Phase 3 study, supporting potential regulatory approval in Japan.

Key Takeaways for Trading/Capital Markets: Positive cash inflow (AU$4.2M) and confirmation of partnership progress. Upside potential from future milestones (up to AU$107M from FUSO alone). Licensing pipeline (AU$1.4B total potential) remains a material valuation driver.

• Drilling commenced at Tumblegum South Gold Project, targeting high-grade lodes and infill drilling to convert inferred to indicated resources.
  • Structural review identified potential for additional high-grade mineralisation near existing resource, possibly increasing resource size.
  • Project economics based on gold prices A$3,000–A$3,800/oz, estimating production of 11.8–15.9koz gold with undiscounted cash surplus of A$9.4M–A$19.6M.
  • Pre-mining capital estimated at A$0.7M–A$1.5M, with potential 18-month mining campaign.
  • Current resource: 616kt @ 2.28g/t Au (45koz), split into indicated (337kt @ 2.52g/t) and inferred (279kt @ 1.99g/t).
  • Next steps: Drill results, mining approvals submission, JORC update, and binding mining agreement with MEGA Resources.

No material capital markets or liquidity impacts identified.
